# Task Lifecycle: Automatic Transitions

This documents every place the task system automatically starts, stops, or closes a task
as a side effect of another action.

## 1. No auto-stop on start

Starting a task does **not** auto-stop other in-progress tasks. Agents are responsible for
explicitly stopping tasks when switching (`aiki task stop --reason "Switching to X"`) or
closing them when done (`aiki task close --summary "..."`).

## 2. Auto-start parent (when last subtask closes)

**Location:** `../commands/task.rs` — `run_close()`

When a subtask is closed and it is the **last unclosed subtask** of a parent, the parent
is automatically started (transitions to InProgress). This prompts the agent to do a
final review/wrap-up of the parent.

- Skips if parent is already Closed or InProgress
- Uses `all_subtasks_closed()` from `manager.rs`

## 3. Stop stale subtasks on parent start

**Location:** `../commands/task.rs` — `run_start()`

When a parent task with subtasks is started, any in-progress subtasks from a
previous (dead) session are stopped. This gives the new session a clean slate.

## 4. Quick-start: create + start atomically

**Location:** `../commands/task.rs` — `run_start()`

When `aiki task start "some description"` receives a non-task-ID string, it creates a
new task with that description and immediately starts it.

## 5. Template quick-start: create from template + start

**Location:** `../commands/task.rs` — `run_start()`

When `aiki task start --template <name>` is used, it creates task(s) from the template
then recursively calls the start flow with the new task ID.

## 6. Auto-start next subtask (on subtask close)

**Location:** `../commands/task.rs` — `run_close()`

When a subtask is closed and the **parent is claimed by the current session**, the next
pending subtask (by priority, then creation order) is automatically started. This only
triggers when the session owns the parent — not when an agent only claimed a single
subtask without the parent.

- Requires: parent `claimed_by_session` matches current session
- Skips if all subtasks are closed (auto-start parent handles that case)
- The auto-started subtask inherits the session claim
- Output includes the started subtask with its instructions

## Summary

| Transition            | Trigger                        | Effect                                  |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| Auto-start parent     | Closing last subtask           | Parent transitions to InProgress        |
| Auto-start next child | Closing subtask (parent owned) | Next pending subtask started            |
| Stop stale subtasks   | Starting parent with subtasks  | In-progress subtasks stopped            |
| Quick-start           | `task start "desc"`            | New task created and started            |
| Template start        | `task start --template X`      | Template task created and started       |

The auto-start-parent and auto-start-next-child logic live in the close handler in `commands/task.rs`.
